    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - MANIFOLDS - Installation</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>When installing the exhaust manifolds, only use prevailing torque flanged-head bolts with
                        interference thread.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="torque" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Right Exhaust Manifold</title>
            <figure id="f1200309" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3311.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="392px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Installing the Right Exhaust Manifold</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Manifold</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Stud Nut</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting Bolt</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply Never-Seez&#174; to the threads of the manifold bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the right exhaust manifold (with gasket if required), seven mounting bolts and
                    one stud nut. Tighten the bolts in the specified sequence to the special torque value.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1200315" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3300.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="392px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Installing the EBP Sensor Tube</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">EBP Sensor Tube</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">EBP Sensor Tube Nut</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Manifold</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If equipped, install the EBP sensor tube to the exhaust manifold and tighten the nut.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the exhaust manifold flange to the turbocharger exhaust tube. Tighten the bolts
                    to the special torque value.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
